# StockResearch вЂ” Product Requirements Document

> For use with Claude Code
> Version 1.1 | Personal use, self-hosted on Synology DS218+

-----

## 1. Overview

StockResearch is a personal, self-hosted web application that wraps the TradingAgents multi-agent framework into a clean UI. It allows the user to submit stock research requests, run AI-powered analysis via the Gemini Flash API, and browse a persistent history of past research runs вЂ” all hosted on a Synology DS218+ NAS via Docker.

-----

## 2. Goals

- Run TradingAgents analysis on any stock ticker with minimal friction
- Default to вЂњtoday minus 3 daysвЂќ as the analysis date, with full custom date support
- Persist every research run to a local SQLite database
- Browse, search, and re-read past runs without re-running (and re-paying) the API
- Deploy as a Docker Compose stack on Synology DS218+

-----

## 3. Non-Goals

- No multi-user support вЂ” single user only, no auth required
- No live trading or brokerage integration
- No real-time stock price feeds
- No mobile-native app вЂ” responsive web is sufficient
- No sector-level screening (single ticker analysis only)

