## 6. Data Model

### `research_runs` table

|Column         |Type      |Notes                                                                    |
|---------------|----------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|id             |INTEGER PK|Auto-increment                                                           |
|ticker         |TEXT      |Uppercase, e.g. вЂњNVDAвЂќ                                                   |
|analysis_date  |DATE      |Date passed to TradingAgents                                             |
|run_timestamp  |DATETIME  |When the run was initiated (UTC)                                         |
|started_at     |DATETIME  |When the background job actually began executing (UTC); used for stale detection|
|status         |TEXT      |`pending` / `running` / `complete` / `failed`                            |
|recommendation |TEXT      |`Buy` / `Overweight` / `Hold` / `Underweight` / `Sell`                   |
|analyst_reports|JSON      |`{ fundamentals, sentiment, news, technical }` вЂ” sourced from `final_state`|
|final_report   |TEXT      |Full Portfolio Manager decision (markdown); includes executive summary, investment thesis, price target, time horizon|
|risk_assessment|JSON      |`risk_debate_state` from `final_state` вЂ” aggressive / conservative / neutral histories + judge decision|
|model_used     |TEXT      |`вЂќdeep=<model>, quick=<model>вЂќ` вЂ” records the two models used for the run|
|error_message  |TEXT      |Populated on failure (truncated traceback)                               |

> **Note:** `confidence` was removed. TradingAgentsвЂ™ `PortfolioDecision` schema has no confidence field. Relevant detail is captured in `final_report` instead.

### `app_config` table (singleton, id = 1)

|Column        |Type |Default          |Notes                              |
|--------------|-----|-----------------|-----------------------------------|
|id            |INTEGER PK|1           |Always 1 вЂ” single config row       |
|deep_think_llm|TEXT |`gemini-2.5-pro` |Model for complex reasoning agents |
|quick_think_llm|TEXT|`gemini-2.5-flash`|Model for faster utility agents   |

SQLite is run in **WAL mode** (`PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL`) to allow safe concurrent reads during background writes.

